.SH NAME
Module::Build::Prereqs::FromCPANfile \- construct prereq parameters of Module::Build from cpanfile
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&    use Module::Build;
\&    use Module::Build::Prereqs::FromCPANfile;
\&    
\&    Module::Build\->new(
\&        ...,
\&        mb_prereqs_from_cpanfile()
\&    )\->create_build_script();
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This simple module reads cpanfile and converts its content into
valid prereq parameters for \f(CWnew()\fR method of Module::Build.
.PP
Currently it does not support "optional features" specification (See "feature" in cpanfile).
.SH "EXPORTED FUNCTION"
.IX Header "EXPORTED FUNCTION"
The following function is exported by default.
.ie n .SS "%prereq_params = mb_prereqs_from_cpanfile(%args)"
.el .SS "\f(CW%prereq_params\fP = mb_prereqs_from_cpanfile(%args)"
.IX Subsection "%prereq_params = mb_prereqs_from_cpanfile(%args)"
Reads cpanfile, parses its content and returns corresponding \f(CW%prereq_params\fR for Module::Build.
.PP
Fields in \f(CW%args\fR are:
.ie n .IP """version"" => VERSION_STR (optional, default: $Module::Build::VERSION)" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWversion\fR => VERSION_STR (optional, default: \f(CW$Module::Build::VERSION\fR)" 4
.IX Item "version => VERSION_STR (optional, default: $Module::Build::VERSION)"
Version number of the target Module::Build.
.Sp
If omitted, Module::Build is loaded and \f(CW$Module::Build::VERSION\fR is used.
.ie n .IP """cpanfile"" => FILEPATH (optional, default: ""cpanfile"")" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWcpanfile\fR => FILEPATH (optional, default: ""cpanfile"")" 4
.IX Item "cpanfile => FILEPATH (optional, default: ""cpanfile"")"
File path to the cpanfile to be loaded.
.Sp
If omitted, it loads "cpanfile" in the current directory.
